<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,152,1978]" box="[199,328,1832,1858]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,152,1978]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">
<taxonomicName box="[199,335,1872,1897]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Brontostoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deferreri" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[199,335,1872,1897]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">B. deferreri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[341,432,1872,1898]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be separated from all the known species by its color pattern. It is the only species with three colors in the pronotum. The hemispherical tubercle on the ventro-posterior side of the head is unique in the genus, and the narrow connexivum is also distinctive.
</paragraph>
