<taxonomicNameLabel box="[394,488,1831,1857]" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be distinguished from the other species in the genus by its uniform brownish black color and orange connexivum. Because the coloration shown by the new species is very peculiar, it is not possible to state which species might be most proximate to 
<taxonomicName box="[909,1099,1912,1937]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Brontostoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diringshofeni" status="sp. nov.">
