<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1109,1204,1911,1937]" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
On the other hand, because the coloration patterns in 
<taxonomicName box="[550,721,1951,1977]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ectrichodiinae">Ectrichodiinae</taxonomicName>
seem to be aposematic, with apparent Müllerian mimicry 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,265,1905,1929]" pageId="10" pageNumber="51">
<collectionCode box="[151,238,1905,1929]" pageId="10" pageNumber="51">PLATE</collectionCode>
